## Bandit Level 9 → Level 10

**Challenge:** The password is stored in `data.txt` in one of the few human-readable strings, preceded by several `=` characters.

**Solution:**
```bash
strings data.txt | grep "="

**Explanation**:

strings data.txt extracts only the human-readable sequences of characters from the binary file

grep "===" filters for lines containing three or more = characters in a row

The password appears after the = signs on the same line

**Password**: FGUW5ilLVJrxX9kMYMmlN4MgbpfMiqey

**What I learned**:

cat and grep alone cannot read binary files properly

strings extracts printable text from any file, even if it contains non-printable data

Piping strings to grep allows searching within binary files

The = characters act as a marker to locate the password line
